 :Trojan horse: [coined by MIT-hacker-turned-NSA-spook Dan Edwards] n. A
program designed to break security or damage a system that is disguised as
something else benign, such as a directory lister, archiver, a game, or (in
one notorious 1990 case on the Mac) a program to find and destroy viruses!
see {back door}, {virus}, {worm}.